The paper deals with the construction of binary codes for error correction, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The problem of correcting deletions involves manipulating data structures, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the redundancy of the codes, which is a topic in coding theory (cs.CC). Finally, the paper mentions the modification of the code to allow for a combination of insertions and deletions, which is a topic in systems and control (cs.SI).
